FBIS4-53888 "dreas100_n_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-100 Daily Report 21 May 1994 Vietnam Australia Spends $6.5 Million To Train Pilots Australia Spends $6.5 Million To Train Pilots BK2305115094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 21 May 94 BK2305115094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] Australia Minister for Development and Cooperation Mr. Gordon Bilney has announced a grant of $6.5 million to train 60 Vietnamese pilots over several years to fly modern jet aircraft. A delegation from Vietnam, led by Vietnam Airlines Human Resources Development Manager Nguyen Sy Hung, recently visited Adelaide for discussion with Qantas and the Australian Aviation College.
